WEBVTT

00:04.134 --> 00:06.006
- Karen!

00:06.745 --> 00:08.660
Uh, K-Kar--Karen...

00:08.704 --> 00:10.097
what's the deal?
Did you not see me?

00:10.140 --> 00:12.273
- Of course I did, but I ran
because your face says

00:12.316 --> 00:14.231
you want money for something.
- Oh, well, yeah, I do.

00:14.275 --> 00:15.406
- What is it today?

00:15.450 --> 00:17.104
Therapy dogs
for postpartum mothers?

00:17.147 --> 00:19.454
Improv classes
for survivors of PTSD?

00:19.497 --> 00:23.066
- No, good idea, both of those,
but I was thinking that--

00:27.549 --> 00:30.160
I want to end systemic racism.
- Oh, for God's sake.

00:30.204 --> 00:32.336
- No, just at the hospital.
Start small, right?

00:32.380 --> 00:34.164
Wow, that's kind of
controversial stance.

00:34.208 --> 00:35.513
Walking away,
siding with racism.

00:35.557 --> 00:36.819
Kind of a Karen move, Karen.

00:36.862 --> 00:38.647
- My exasperation with you
has no relation

00:38.690 --> 00:41.345
to my thoughts on racism.

00:41.389 --> 00:42.781
Why today, Max?

00:42.825 --> 00:44.348
- Knew you were
gonna ask that,

00:44.392 --> 00:45.610
but there is no answer,
because we should be asking

00:46.698 --> 00:47.308
the right question,
which is why not yesterday?

00:47.830 --> 00:48.700
Why not a year ago?

00:49.745 --> 00:50.659
Why not two years ago
when I first took over?

00:51.703 --> 00:52.835
Systemic racism should
have been the first thing

00:53.792 --> 00:54.576
I addressed
when I got to New Amsterdam,

00:55.316 --> 00:56.143
and I'm appalled
that it wasn't,

00:57.144 --> 00:58.623
so today it is.
- And you need money for...

00:58.667 --> 01:01.278
- A new position,
someone to help us identify

01:01.322 --> 01:03.237
and eliminate
systemic marginalization

01:03.280 --> 01:05.543
while correcting inequities
throughout the whole hospital.

01:05.587 --> 01:07.458
- You want
a chief equity officer?

01:07.502 --> 01:09.634
- Yeah, that's perfect.
We'll call it that.

01:09.678 --> 01:12.420
Oh, and I am not going anywhere
until you give me one.

01:12.463 --> 01:17.164
- Well, in that case, go away,
because we already have one.

01:17.207 --> 01:18.556
- We do?

01:21.864 --> 01:24.823
<i>♪</i>

01:24.867 --> 01:26.738
- Hey.
- Oh, hi there.

01:26.782 --> 01:31.308
Are you--let's see here--
Isabel?

01:31.352 --> 01:32.570
- Yes.

01:32.614 --> 01:33.745
- Great, I'm Max Goodwin,
medical director.

01:33.789 --> 01:35.573
- How can I help?

01:35.617 --> 01:37.575
- I see what you did there.

01:37.619 --> 01:40.578
Um, yeah, I'm here to discuss

01:40.622 --> 01:42.885
some pretty disturbing
statistics.

01:42.928 --> 01:44.669
- Hit me.
- Okay.

01:44.713 --> 01:46.367
Well, according to
the latest report

01:46.410 --> 01:47.411
by Health and Human Services,

01:47.455 --> 01:50.153
Latinx women
are 40% more likely

01:50.197 --> 01:52.373
to have cervical cancer
and 20% more likely

01:52.416 --> 01:54.288
to die from it
than white women.

01:54.331 --> 01:57.247
Indigenous Americans have twice
the HIV infection rate

01:57.291 --> 01:58.944
as that
of non-Hispanic whites.

01:58.988 --> 02:02.252
Black women are
two to six times more likely

02:02.296 --> 02:03.645
to die from complications
of pregnancy

02:03.688 --> 02:05.516
than white women.

02:05.560 --> 02:08.780
- Actually, it's 12 times
more likely in New York City.

02:08.824 --> 02:11.566
Your statistics
are a bit...generic.

02:11.609 --> 02:12.958
- Oh.

02:13.002 --> 02:15.265
How long have you worked here?
- Three years.

02:15.309 --> 02:18.442
- Three--three years?

02:18.486 --> 02:20.749
Well, we have
a lot of work to do.

02:20.792 --> 02:24.883
- That's exactly what
I say to you in my messages.

02:24.927 --> 02:26.798
Once a week, I leave word
with your office

02:26.842 --> 02:28.713
hoping to get
some time with you.

02:30.498 --> 02:32.369
- Sorry, you know,
sometimes with this hospital,

02:32.413 --> 02:34.284
I'm just running
and--not important.

02:34.328 --> 02:38.245
Listen, I'm here now, okay?
- Okay.

02:38.288 --> 02:41.552
- And we are gonna fix this,
so I want innovative proposals

02:41.596 --> 02:44.468
on my desk by tomorrow,
and think big.

02:44.512 --> 02:47.428
You know, get creative.
No solution is off the table.

02:47.471 --> 02:49.256
- Should we start
with acknowledging

02:49.299 --> 02:50.866
New Amsterdam's
biggest illustration

02:50.909 --> 02:52.911
of embedded systemic racism?

02:52.955 --> 02:54.826
- Yes, yes, of course.
What is it?

02:54.870 --> 02:56.480
- You.

02:56.524 --> 03:02.530
<i>♪</i>

03:02.573 --> 03:04.880
- Good read?
- Don't get me started.

03:04.923 --> 03:06.621
Actually, do get me started.

03:06.664 --> 03:08.536
I've been made executor
of my brother's will,

03:08.579 --> 03:10.233
and I haven't the foggiest.

03:10.277 --> 03:11.800
- I thought you two
weren't close.

03:11.843 --> 03:13.497
- Well, we weren't, but now
I'm in charge of his house,

03:13.541 --> 03:15.325
his car, his saxophones.

03:15.369 --> 03:17.675
I mean, the only thing
I'm confident about

03:17.719 --> 03:18.937
is making arrangements
for his daughter Mina

03:18.981 --> 03:19.982
to live with her aunt
in Dubai..

03:20.025 --> 03:21.853
in an actual palace.

03:21.897 --> 03:23.420
- You have a niece.

03:23.464 --> 03:24.682
- And apparently
a rich second aunt

03:24.726 --> 03:25.770
who doesn't want
my brother's boat

03:25.814 --> 03:27.294
because she
already has several.

03:27.337 --> 03:28.425
- Well, you keep it.

03:28.469 --> 03:30.514
We could spend
our vacation at sea.

03:30.558 --> 03:33.474
Sky, the waves, you and me.

03:33.517 --> 03:35.650
- It's a rowboat.

03:35.693 --> 03:37.347
- Then Bora Bora it is.

03:37.391 --> 03:39.262
<i>♪</i>

03:39.306 --> 03:41.569
- So did you like the rest
of "Catcher in the Rye"?

03:42.918 --> 03:44.485
What about
that red hunting hat, man?

03:44.528 --> 03:46.400
I thought that would be
right up your alley.

03:46.443 --> 03:49.446
- Mm, it was fine.
- It was fine.

03:49.490 --> 03:52.754
You talked my ear off
about the Ducks last session.

03:52.797 --> 03:54.408
The red hunting hat
is way more important.

03:56.018 --> 03:58.760
Oh, I'm sorry.
What's up with your hand?

03:58.803 --> 04:01.806
- I-I fell on it wrong.
- Oh, okay.

04:01.850 --> 04:03.286
Well, just in case,
let me take a look.

04:03.330 --> 04:04.896
- It's fine.

04:04.940 --> 04:06.811
- That's a little
too much "fine"

04:06.855 --> 04:10.293
for one session, Ollie.
Let me see.

04:10.337 --> 04:12.991
<i>♪</i>

04:13.035 --> 04:14.602
<i>- Radiology's slammed,</i>

04:14.645 --> 04:15.733
but they'll fit him
in right away.

04:15.777 --> 04:17.344
- Okay, thank you.
See that, buddy?

04:17.387 --> 04:18.910
VIP treatment for you,
all right?

04:18.954 --> 04:20.434
- What happened?

04:20.477 --> 04:27.441
<i>♪</i>

04:30.095 --> 04:32.750
- Uh, he said he fell.

04:32.794 --> 04:35.362
- No, Mama, last night,
I separated them all

04:35.405 --> 04:36.798
and put them
in your monthly pill organizer,

04:36.841 --> 04:38.756
remember?

04:38.800 --> 04:40.976
Yes, of course you can still
call me whenever you want.

04:41.019 --> 04:43.370
But, no, but take
the yellow pill now.

04:43.413 --> 04:45.546
The yellow pill
while I'm on the phone.

04:46.982 --> 04:48.592
- Incoming!

04:48.636 --> 04:50.507
- A tour bus jumped the curb
in Times Square.

04:50.551 --> 04:52.335
Superman may have
a fractured wrist,

04:52.379 --> 04:54.119
but he won't stay put long
enough for me to check.

04:54.163 --> 04:55.120
- Yeah, okay,
what's his real name?

04:55.164 --> 04:56.600
- ID says Murph Coleman,

04:56.644 --> 04:59.124
but he only responds
to Superman.

04:59.168 --> 05:01.475
Kebir Abad, 38-year-old male
falafel vendor.

05:01.518 --> 05:04.086
Second-degree hot oil burns
covering both arms.

05:04.129 --> 05:05.566
- Superman,
get back in your chair.

05:05.609 --> 05:06.871
- Not till this man's
in bay 24!

05:06.915 --> 05:08.960
- Hammond!
- On it.

05:09.004 --> 05:11.093
- Skelly, Williams,
team three, bed five.

05:11.136 --> 05:12.703
- Hey, you gotta
hold this, okay?

05:12.747 --> 05:14.052
It's important.
- Stable vitals?

05:14.096 --> 05:15.837
Team one, bed nine.
- You okay?

05:15.880 --> 05:17.360
You gotta keep your eyes open.

05:17.404 --> 05:19.362
- Someone get me Cassian.
- All right.

05:19.406 --> 05:20.798
- Let's do it.
- You gonna be okay?

05:20.842 --> 05:22.713
- Gotta go.
- I-I can't--

05:22.757 --> 05:24.411
- Come on,
let's not back up triage.

05:24.454 --> 05:25.412
Hammond.

05:26.674 --> 05:27.805
- Hammond!
- Sorry.

05:27.849 --> 05:29.459
He really is faster than a--

05:29.503 --> 05:31.592
- Do not!
Just get him back in his chair.

05:31.635 --> 05:33.507
- Wilmer Belasco, male,
42 years old.

05:33.550 --> 05:35.073
Blunt force trauma
to the chest.

05:35.117 --> 05:38.860
Heart rate 113, BP 161 over 98.
Possible cracked sternum.

05:38.903 --> 05:40.078
- My boy--
- Don't try to talk.

05:40.122 --> 05:41.602
Mr. Belasco.
- Hector Belasco,

05:41.645 --> 05:43.560
13-year-old boy.
BP 126 over 87.

05:43.604 --> 05:45.997
- That's my son!
- Lauren, I got him.

05:46.041 --> 05:48.086
-
- Doc, no!

05:48.130 --> 05:49.740
- Sir, he's gonna be
taken care of.

05:49.784 --> 05:51.829
- Hi, Hector, I'm Dr. Shin.
It's okay.

05:51.873 --> 05:53.135
We're gonna take
very good care of you.

05:53.178 --> 05:55.050
- Bilateral compound
femur fracture,

05:55.093 --> 05:56.704
possible hypovolemic shock
from crush injuries.

05:56.747 --> 05:58.488
- Okay, let's take a look.

06:03.014 --> 06:04.407
- Trauma one.

06:04.451 --> 06:07.367
- Dad!
-

06:09.456 --> 06:11.501
- Sir.

06:15.070 --> 06:16.506
- In the chair, Superman.
- But I just--

06:16.550 --> 06:18.421
- Stay put.

06:22.469 --> 06:24.688
<i>-</i>

06:26.211 --> 06:29.127
- Mina, um,
so just give me a second to--

06:40.574 --> 06:42.184
- Mina, I know that it's hard,

06:42.227 --> 06:44.534
but I'm sure your dad would've
wanted you to be with family.

06:44.578 --> 06:47.058
- You know nothing
about my father.

06:50.235 --> 06:52.455
- Can I talk to you a second?
- Can it wait?

06:52.499 --> 06:53.674
I just got--
- No.

06:53.717 --> 06:55.589
I just made a commitment
to ending

06:55.632 --> 06:57.634
the inherent and systemic
racism here at this hospital,

06:57.678 --> 07:00.507
and I know what I need to do.
- Max--

07:00.550 --> 07:02.857
- I'm stepping down
as medical director.

07:02.900 --> 07:04.685
- Who is taking over?

07:04.728 --> 07:05.903
<i>♪</i>

07:05.947 --> 07:08.515
- You are.

07:11.387 --> 07:13.345
- You want me
to be medical director?

07:14.390 --> 07:15.522
- Yeah.
- And you, you'll just--

07:15.565 --> 07:17.393
- Quietly recede
into a supporting role.

07:17.437 --> 07:19.177
- You've never done
anything quietly.

07:19.221 --> 07:21.179
- Yeah, I know.
That's exactly the problem.

07:21.223 --> 07:22.746
I tried to force an initiative
on Black barber shops

07:22.790 --> 07:24.661
to get them to turn
into community health ops.

07:24.705 --> 07:27.272
I have called the WHO
every single day

07:27.316 --> 07:29.187
for three months--
three months--

07:29.231 --> 07:31.451
trying to get racism coded
as a health risk,

07:31.494 --> 07:34.149
and now I realize
that none of it

07:34.192 --> 07:36.194
was ever actually
gonna change anything,

07:36.238 --> 07:37.674
because I am part
of the problem.

07:37.718 --> 07:40.155
- Says who?
- My chief equity officer.

07:40.198 --> 07:41.678
- We have
a chief equity officer?

07:41.722 --> 07:43.550
- Yeah, Isabel.
She's very sweet.

07:43.593 --> 07:46.204
But as women of color,
you are both vastly under--hi.

07:46.248 --> 07:48.555
Underrepresented in management,

07:48.598 --> 07:50.382
which makes you
much less likely

07:50.426 --> 07:52.428
to get a promotion
and therefore not in a position

07:52.472 --> 07:54.604
to then hire
other women of color,

07:54.648 --> 07:56.693
so it's a vicious cycle really,

07:56.737 --> 07:58.739
but the thing is
it can be changed

07:58.782 --> 08:00.392
if a woman of color
is at the top,

08:00.436 --> 08:03.308
which is exactly why you
need to say yes to this job.

08:03.352 --> 08:06.094
- No.
- You could do a lot of good.

08:06.137 --> 08:07.269
- Here I thought
I was doing good

08:07.312 --> 08:09.532
being an oncologist.
- More good.

08:09.576 --> 08:11.795
- Do you not see the irony

08:11.839 --> 08:13.710
in asking someone
who's suffering

08:13.754 --> 08:16.452
from systemic racism
to also fix it?

08:17.322 --> 08:19.760
- Well, does that mean
you'll consider it?

08:19.803 --> 08:21.457
Okay, no, Helen, I--

08:21.501 --> 08:23.154
ugh, I don't know
where to start!

08:23.198 --> 08:24.416
- Just look to your right.

08:27.463 --> 08:34.165
<i>♪</i>

08:34.905 --> 08:36.559
- Hey, you are
gonna be just fine.

08:36.603 --> 08:37.778
- I got him down
in a wheelchair,

08:37.821 --> 08:39.388
but he got up again.
- Here we go!

08:39.431 --> 08:40.563
- Superman!

08:40.607 --> 08:42.696
- Have Walsh
clear Superman's wrist

08:42.739 --> 08:44.567
and escort him
out of here, okay?

08:44.611 --> 08:46.700
Where am I going?
- Hey--

08:46.743 --> 08:48.266
- Hey, this has to get
to the trauma room.

08:48.310 --> 08:49.746
- This is Mr. Abad.

08:49.790 --> 08:51.443
Before his car flipped over,

08:51.487 --> 08:52.793
he saw the whole accident.
- Hammond, you're killing me.

08:54.011 --> 08:55.535
Do not let him into trauma one.
- Doing the best I can.

08:55.578 --> 08:56.536
- Right here.

08:57.624 --> 08:59.147
Uhh--hey!

08:59.190 --> 09:00.583
- Right before
his car tipped over,

09:00.627 --> 09:01.802
he saw the whole accident.

09:01.845 --> 09:03.760
Tell Dr. Bloom
what you just told me.

09:03.804 --> 09:05.762
- It was the craziest thing
I've ever seen.

09:05.806 --> 09:07.764
The minute the bus
jumped the curb,

09:07.808 --> 09:11.159
everybody started running,
except for Superman.

09:13.770 --> 09:16.468
He just stood there.
- Why?

09:16.512 --> 09:19.254
- No idea, but he took the hit
like a champ.

09:19.297 --> 09:21.212
I hope someone got video.

09:22.649 --> 09:25.565
- Superman got hit by the bus?
- Hard.

09:25.608 --> 09:27.479
I don't know
he's still standing.

09:27.523 --> 09:31.396
- Well, he is the Man of St--
- Don't say it.

09:31.440 --> 09:32.615
Page neurology now.

09:32.659 --> 09:35.749
<i>♪</i>

09:35.792 --> 09:37.446
- I've got 52 bones.

09:37.489 --> 09:41.842
<i>♪</i>

09:41.885 --> 09:44.322
- Did you hear
that Ollie hurt his hand?

09:44.366 --> 09:46.368
- Yes.

09:46.411 --> 09:48.892
- It's really bad.

09:48.936 --> 09:52.853
I'm a doctor, and I can't
even figure out what happened.

09:52.896 --> 09:55.507
- I'm not stupid.
I know you think I did it.

09:55.551 --> 09:58.206
- Did you?

09:58.249 --> 10:01.252
- I had to.
I had no choice.

10:01.296 --> 10:04.429
<i>♪</i>

10:04.473 --> 10:06.649
- Juliet, you were making
such progress.

10:06.693 --> 10:10.305
- He insulted my brother,
my parents.

10:10.348 --> 10:12.394
I was defending their honor.

10:12.437 --> 10:14.004
- You were defending
their honor?

10:14.048 --> 10:16.354
- When I took
the vow of the samurai,

10:16.398 --> 10:19.793
I took the vow to the death.
- Is this a joke to you?

10:19.836 --> 10:23.274
- Sure,
because I didn't do it.

10:23.318 --> 10:25.625
- Okay.

10:25.668 --> 10:27.583
Juliet, do you remember
the rules of the game

10:27.627 --> 10:30.673
that we've been playing?
- Expert level.

10:30.717 --> 10:32.849
I only win if the loser
doesn't think they lost.

10:32.893 --> 10:36.461
If I upset them or hurt them,
I lose.

10:36.505 --> 10:38.507
- Correct.

10:38.550 --> 10:41.597
So when you smashed
Ollie's hand, you lost.

10:41.641 --> 10:45.427
- Except I didn't
smash Ollie's hand.

10:45.470 --> 10:47.385
I was joking.

10:47.429 --> 10:49.257
- I don't think
you're telling the truth.

10:51.389 --> 10:52.608
- Right now or before?
- Now.

10:52.652 --> 10:54.697
I think you're lying
to protect yourself.

10:54.741 --> 10:57.308
- Final answer?
- This is not a game, Juliet.

10:57.352 --> 10:59.920
This is not the game!

11:04.402 --> 11:06.056
Okay.

11:06.100 --> 11:10.582
<i>♪</i>

11:10.626 --> 11:13.281
I'm sorry.
I shouldn't have yelled.

11:13.324 --> 11:15.500
- It wasn't very professional.

11:18.895 --> 11:19.940
- Okay.

11:21.811 --> 11:23.639
Here's what I want.

11:25.554 --> 11:27.425
I want you to tell me
one true thing

11:27.469 --> 11:29.732
about Ollie's hand.

11:29.776 --> 11:31.995
One true thing, that's it.

11:36.826 --> 11:38.610
- Luisa did it.

11:38.654 --> 11:41.657
<i>♪</i>

11:41.701 --> 11:43.877
- Luisa.

11:47.663 --> 11:51.754
<i>♪</i>

11:51.798 --> 11:54.714
Luisa, hi.

11:54.757 --> 11:57.325
Can I see you
for a second please?

11:59.980 --> 12:01.808
- My wrist feels fine.

12:01.851 --> 12:03.853
I'd love to get back downstairs
in case anyone needs my help.

12:03.897 --> 12:05.333
<i>- They don't.</i>

12:05.376 --> 12:07.770
I need you to hold still.

12:11.600 --> 12:13.384
What?
- I was just wondering

12:13.428 --> 12:14.995
why he annoys you so much.

12:15.038 --> 12:17.127
- Everyone annoys me this much.

12:17.171 --> 12:19.739
- Good to know.

12:19.782 --> 12:21.784
- The world's a disaster
right now.

12:21.828 --> 12:24.004
We all need to pitch in
to try to fix it.

12:24.047 --> 12:27.747
Got no patience for someone
dressing up pretending to.

12:30.924 --> 12:33.491
Well, there's no fractures
or internal damage

12:33.535 --> 12:35.929
to his legs or trunk.
- It's crazy.

12:37.800 --> 12:40.760
It's like he's made of steel.
- He's not.

12:40.803 --> 12:41.761
Look.

12:44.851 --> 12:47.810
- A brain bleed.

12:47.854 --> 12:50.508
<i>♪</i>

12:52.815 --> 12:53.903
- Mina.

12:58.560 --> 13:00.605
<i>- You were right.</i>

13:00.649 --> 13:02.390
I don't know
the first thing about you,

13:02.433 --> 13:04.827
but, uh, I want to.

13:04.871 --> 13:06.524
I really do.

13:06.568 --> 13:10.659
So, please,
can we just try again?

13:20.800 --> 13:24.542
<i>♪</i>

13:24.586 --> 13:26.022
- Really? Um...

13:27.502 --> 13:29.939
Mina, you're 16.
- 16, so what?

13:29.983 --> 13:31.854
- So marriage
is a big decision,

13:31.898 --> 13:33.638
and it should really only come
from wanting

13:33.682 --> 13:36.467
to spend the rest
of your life with someone.

